TestHandledFlagSetWhenRecoverySucceeds
/ When error.handle's recovery body completes successfully, the recovery suppresses the error, %!error% is restored to null after the scope closes, and downstream code continues.
- throw error "boom", on error set %recovered% = true
- assert %recovered% is true, "recovery body should have run"
- assert %!error% is null, "error scope closed — %!error% restores to null"
